cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the analysis of social media data and the use of social sensing to study offline phenomena. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it discusses the development of techniques to improve now-casting performance. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it explores the impact of social media on society and how it can be used for public health and economic monitoring. It may also fall under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) as it deals with the analysis of social networks and their impact on offline phenomena. Finally, it could be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it discusses the selection of user groups for more accurate now-casting.
